include ../../tlMatter.pug
if docLang === "EN"
  mixin tl(tlText)
    if tlText != null
      +inlineTl("EN", tlText)
    else
      +inlineTl("EN")
        block
    
  mixin tlDb(key)
    case key
      when "PresentTense"
        | Present Tense
      when "OrdinaryPresentTense"
        | Present Habitual Tense
      when "PastTense"
        | Past Tense
      when "PastHabitualTense"
        | Past Habitual Tense
      when "FutureTense"
        | Future Tense
      when "ConditionalMood"
        | Conditional Mood
      when "SubjunctiveMood"
        | Subjunctive Mood
      when "PresentSubjunctiveMood"
        | Present Subjunctive Mood
      when "ImperativeMood"
        | Imperative Mood
      when "IndicativeMood"
        | Indicative Mood
      when "VerbalNoun"
        | Verbal Noun
      when "VerbalAdjective"
        | Verbal Adjective
      when "teidealNaCaibidle"
        | The Verb

      when "5-1-title"
        | The Regular Verbs
      when "5-title"
        | #[+renderKey("Caibidil", { getFromCommon: true })] 5 | #[+renderKey("teidealNaCaibidle")]
      when "5-1-1-p"
        | There are two conjugations for regular verbs.
      when "5-1-2-p"
        | The First Conjugation applies to:
      when "5-1-2-a-p"
        | verbs of monosyllabic roots, e.g., #[i bog], #[i bris], #[i caith], #[i mol], including verbs ending in #[i igh], e.g., #[i breoigh], #[i clóigh], #[i cráigh], #[i iaigh], #[i luaigh], #[i reoigh], #[i sáigh];
      when "5-1-2-b-p"
        | verbs of polysyllabic roots ending in #[i áil], e.g., #[i sábháil], #[i tarrtháil], and some particular polysyllabic verbs, e.g., #[i adhlaic], #[i ceiliúir], #[i gearán], #[i seachaid], #[i taispeáin], #[i tíolaic].
      when "5-1-3-p"
        | The Second Conjugation applies to:
      when "5-1-3-a-p"
        | verbs with polysyllabic roots ending in #[i -(a)igh], e.g., #[i ceannaigh], #[i imigh]
      when "5-1-3-b-p"
        | verbs with polysyllabic roots ending in #[i -(a)il], #[i -(a)in], #[i -(a)ir], #[i -(a)is] and syncopated in the conjugation, e.g., #[i agair], #[i codail], #[i cogain], #[i iompair], #[i tochail];
      when "5-1-3-c-p"
        | a small number of particular verbs such as #[i foghlaim], #[i fulaing], #[i tarraing], #[i tuirling].
      when "5-1-4-p"
        | The conjugation of a compound verb is usually the same as that of the verb from which it is formed:
      when "5-1-4-a-p"
        | #[i aisíoc], #[i athdhear] and #[i comhlíon] in the first conjugation are similar to #[i íoc], #[i dear] and #[i líon]; and
      when "5-1-4-b-p"
        | #[i athchomhairligh], #[i comhdhlúthaigh] and #[i comhshínigh] in the second conjugation are similar to #[i comhairligh], #[i dlúthaigh] and #[i sínigh].
      when "5-1-5-title"
        | The Subjunctive Mood
      when "5-1-5-a-p"
        | If a sentence has a optative function, it is always in the subjunctive mood, e.g., #[i Go raibh maith agat] #[+tl Thank you (lit. may goodness be at you)]; #[i Go dté tú slán] #[+tl May you go safely]. There is a choice between the present subjunctive mood and the future tense when the verb of the main clause is in the primary tense in the following contexts:
      when "5-1-5-a-i-p"
        | after the temporal conjuctions #[i ach a] #[+tl as soon as], #[i go] #[+tl until], #[i nó go] #[+tl until], #[i sula] #[+tl before], e.g., #[i Gheobhaimid an scéal ceart ach a dtaga] (#[i a dtiocfaidh]) #[i Pól] #[+tl We will get the right story as soon as Paul comes]; #[i Ná beannaigh don diabhal go mbeannaí] (#[i go mbeannóidh]) #[i sé duit] (#[b EN]: #[i Do not greet the devil until he greets you] (see #[+link("https://www.teanglann.ie/en/fgb/diabhal", "FGB entry")(target="blank")])); #[i Beidh tú ann nó go bhfása] (#[i nó go bhfásfaidh]) #[i coincleach ort] #[+tl You will be there until mold will grow on you]; #[i Beidh siad ann sula mbuailtear] (#[i sula mbuailfear]) #[i clog an aingil] #[+tl They will be there before the angel&rsquo;s bell is struck].
      when "5-1-5-a-ii-p"
        | after the conjunction of purpose #[+tl so that] #[i go], #[i nó go], e.g., #[i Féach é go bhfeice] (#[i go bhfeicfidh]) #[i tú] #[+tl Look at it so that you may see it]; #[i Suigh nó go raibh] (#[i nó go mbeidh]) #[i do scíth déanta agat] #[+tl Sit so that you may have rested];
      when "5-1-5-a-iii-p"
        | in the first open clause after #[i mura] #[+tl if not], e.g., #[i Mura gcuire] (#[i mura gcuirfidh]) #[i tú], #[i ní bhainfidh tú] #[+tl If you do not put, you will not gain].
      when "5-1-5-b-i-p"
        | The forms of the past subjunctive mood are the same as the forms of the dependent past habitual tense (except for the verb #[i bí]) (see the Dependent Form, #[+link("#sec_5_1_8", "5.1.8")]). The conditional mood&rsquo;s form can also be used instead of the past subjunctive if the main clause is in the past tense, the past habitual tense or the conditional mood, e.g., #[i Tháinig] (#[i thagadh], #[i thiocfadh]) #[i sí aír preo fíctí] (#[i bhfécfí]) #[i í] #[+tl She came in before she would have seen it]. For the verb #[i bí], the forms of the past subjunctive mood are the same as the conditional mood.
      when "5-1-5-b-ii-p"
        | In the tables in this chapter, the present subjunctive mood is indicated by the particle #[i go]. Although eclipsis follows that particle and some others, this is not true for every particle accompanying the subjunctive mood. Lenition follows #[i nár], e.g., #[i Nár fhana sé i bhfad] #[+tl He did not stay long].
      when "5-1-6-title"
        | The Negative Particle
      when "5-1-6-p"
        | #[i ní] (#[i níor]) is the negative particle and is shown in the tables where the negative form is given.
      when "5-1-7-title"
        | The Independent Form
      when "5-1-7-p"
        | The independent form is the form of the verb used in an affirmative explicative principal clause, e.g., #[i bhí mé] #[+tl I was]; #[i ceannóidh sé] #[+tl He will buy]; #[i mholfadh sí] #[+tl She would praise]. Unless otherwise stated, it is the independent form that is given in the conjugations in the rest of this chapter, except in the Present Subjunctive Mood.
      when "5-1-8-title"
        | The Dependent Form
      when "5-1-8-p"
        | The dependent form follows these conjunctions, relative pronominals and verbs: #[i a/ar] (= the relative particle), #[i a/ar] (= #[i an méid a/ar] #[+tl the size/extent]), #[i an/ar], #[i cá/cár], #[i dá/dár], (#[i de] or #[i do] + #[i a] (#[i ar])) and #[i dá] (conditional), #[i go/gur], #[i mura/murar], #[i nach/nár], #[i ní/níor], #[i sula/sular] (see #[+link("./chapter10.html#sec_10_4_2", "10.4.2")] and #[+link("./chapter10.html#sec_10_8_2", "10.8.2")]).
      when "5-1-8-note"
        | The forms ending in #[i -r] above are used only in the past tense (but see #[+link("./chapter5-en.html#sec_5_4_5", "5.4.5")]).
      when "5-1-9-title"
        | Verb Tense for #[i má] and #[i nuair]
      when "5-1-9-p"
        | The present habitual tense is followed by #[i má] to express a future condition, e.g., #[i Déanfaidh mé um thráthnóna é má bhíonn deis agam] #[+tl I will do it in the evening if I have the opportunity]. The future tense is what follows #[i nuair] if it is something that will be happening in the future, e.g., #[i Glan é nuair a thiocfaidh tú isteach amárach] #[+tl Clean it when you come in tomorrow].
      when "5-1-10-title"
        | #[i Muid]
      when "5-1-10-p"
        | #[i muid] #[+tl we] can be used with the analytic form of the verb in the first person plural in preference to the conjugated forms of the verb (given in the tables) in all moods and tenses. The analytic form #[i muid] and the conjugated forms of the verb in the first person plural have the same status.
      when "Table5A-caption"
        | The Analytic Form #[i muid]
      when "Table5A-col1"
        | Tense/Mood
      when "Table5A-col2"
        | Analytic Form + #[i muid]
      when "Table5A-col3"
        | Conjugated Form of the Verb
      when "briathar-Mol"
        | Praise
      when "briathar-Bris"
        | Break
      when "5-2-title"
        | The First Conjugation
      when "5-2-1-title"
        | Verbs from monosyllabic roots ending in a consonant other than #[i -gh]
      when "Table5B-caption"
        | The First Conjugation &#8212; Conjugation of the Verb #[i mol]
      when "Table5C-caption"
        | The First Conjugation &#8212; Conjugation of the Verb #[i bris]
      when "Table5C-Note"
        | The independent verb is lenited in the indicative mood for past tense (other than the autonomous verb) and for past habitual tense, and in the conditional mood. There is more information in #[+link("./chapter10.html#sec_10_4", "10.4")] about the other contexts in which the dependent and independent verb is lenited and the contexts in which the verb is eclipsed are discussed in #[+link("./chapter10.html#sec_10_8", "10.8")].
      when "briathar-Sábháil"
        | Save
      when "briathar-Tíolaic"
        | Show
      when "5-2-1-a-p"
        | Regular verbs from monosyllabic roots ending in a broad consonant are formed in the same way as #[i mol], and regular verbs are formed from monosyllabic roots ending in a slender consonant in the same way as #[i bris].
      when "5-2-1-b-p"
        | If a root ending in #[i -t] or #[i -th] (e.g., #[i at], #[i loit], #[i caith], #[i leath]) joins an affix beginning with #[i -t] (e.g., #[i -tar/-tear], #[i -taí/-tí], #[i -tá/-tá], #[i -ta/-te]), the #[i -t(h)t-] becomes #[i -t-]:
      when "5-2-1-b-Table-col1"
        | Ends in broad #[i -t(h)]
      when "5-2-1-b-Table-col2"
        | Ends in slender #[i -t(h)]
      when "5-2-1-c-p"
        | If a root ending in #[i -bh] or #[i -mh] (e.g., #[i gabh], #[i ríomh]) joins an affix beginning with #[i -th-] (e.g., #[i -tha] in the verbal adjective), the #[i -bhth-] or #[i -mhth-] becomes #[i -f-]:
      when "EndsWith"
        | Ends with
      when "5-2-1-d-p"
        | #[i -bh], #[i -mh] and #[i -th] are retained before #[i -f-], e.g., #[i scríobhfaí], #[i ríomhfá], #[i chaithfeá]:
      when "5-2-2-title"
        | Verbs from Polysyllabic Roots
      when "Table5D-caption"
        | The First Conjugation &mdash; Conjugation of the Verb #[i sábháil]
      when "Table5D-note"
        | As for verbs ending in #[i -áil], note that these forms with #[i -t-] are slender, e.g., #[i athchúrsáiltear], #[i d&rsquo;athchúrsáiltí], #[i athchúrsáilte]; #[i sábháiltear], #[i shábháiltí], #[i sábháilte], but the forms with #[i -f-] are broad, e.g., #[i athchúrsálfar], #[i d&rsquo;athchúrsálfaí]; #[i sábhálfar], #[i shábhálfaí].
      when "Table5E-caption"
        | The First Conjugation &mdash; Conjugation of the Verb #[i tíolaic]
      when "5-2-2-tables-col1"
