      when "5-2-2-c-p"
        | Verbs that are kept slender throughout (excluding the verbal noun) in their conjugation:
      when "5-2-2-d-p"
        | Verbs that are kept broad throughout in their conjugation:
      when "5-2-2-note"
        | The verbs from the roots #[i adhain], #[i adhair] and #[i sleabhac] are syncopated as if #[i adhn-], #[i adhr-], #[i sleabhc-], were their root, e.g., #[i adhnann sé], #[i adhrfaidh sí], #[i sleabhctha], except in the analytic past tense, e.g., #[i d&rsquo;adhain sé], #[i d&rsquo;adhair sí], #[i shleabhac siad], and in verbal adjectives #[i adhain], #[i adhair], e.g., #[i adhainte], #[i adhartha].
      when "5-2-3-title"
        | Verbs from monosyllabic roots ending in #[i -gh]
