      when "5-4-title"
        | The Irregular Verbs
      when "5-4-1-p"
        | There are eleven irregular verbs. The following are the irregular verbs: #[i abair] #[+tl say], #[i beir] #[+tl bear], #[i bí] #[+tl be], #[i clois/cluin] #[+tl hear], #[i déan] #[+tl do/make], #[i faigh] #[+tl get], #[i feic] #[+tl see], #[i ith] #[+tl eat], #[i tabhair] #[+tl give], #[i tar] #[+tl come], #[i téigh] #[+tl go].
      when "5-4-2-p"
        | The irregular verbs do not keep the same root throughout their formation and some of them have separate forms in the dependent form.
      when "5-4-3-p"
        | The root of the verb in the present habitual and past habitual tenses is the same in all irregular verbs, e.g., #[i cloisimid], #[i chloisimis] (#[b EN]: #[i we hear], #[i we used to hear]); #[i deirim], #[i deirinn] (#[b EN]: #[i I say], #[i I used to say]); #[i tugann sí], #[i thugadh sí] (#[b EN]: #[i she gives], #[i she used to give]). Except for the verb #[i bí] #[+tl be], the present subjunctive also has the same root, e.g., #[i go gcloise] #[+tl that we hear]; #[i go ndeire] #[+tl that I say]; #[i go dtuga] #[+tl that she gives].
      when "5-4-4-p"
        | The root of the verb in the future tense and the conditional mood is the same in all irregular verbs, e.g., #[i déarfaidh mé] #[+tl I will say], #[i déarfainn] #[+tl I would say]; #[i déanfaidh tú] #[+tl you will do/make], #[i dhéanfá] #[+tl you would do/make]; #[i tabharfaidh siad] #[+tl they will give], #[i thabharfaidís] #[+tl they would give].
      when "5-4-5-title"
